                <h2>Post-Covid Hair Fall vs Other Conditions — How to Differentiate</h2>
                <p>Sometimes, hair loss that appears to be "post-covid" may actually be caused by something else. Covid can sometimes trigger or expose underlying conditions:</p>

                <p><strong>Thyroid issues:</strong> Covid can disrupt thyroid function. If hair fall is accompanied by weight changes, fatigue, or cold sensitivity, be sure to get a thyroid test. <strong>Iron deficiency anemia:</strong> Covid can turn a pre-existing mild deficiency into a severe one. If hair fall is accompanied by fatigue, pale skin, or breathlessness, get a CBC and ferritin test. <strong>Androgenetic alopecia triggered by Covid:</strong> In some individuals, Covid can activate or accelerate genetic hair loss. If hair fall follows a specific pattern, such as a receding hairline or crown thinning, this is different from post-covid Telogen Effluvium. <strong>Alopecia Areata:</strong> In rare cases, the immune system may begin attacking hair follicles after Covid. If you notice patchy bald spots, consult a doctor immediately.</p>

                <p>If you are unsure whether your hair loss is solely post-covid or involves other factors, we strongly recommend seeking a <a href="../contact.php">professional consultation</a>. Blood tests and trichoscopy will provide an accurate diagnosis.</p>

                <h2>Recovery Diet Plan — Specifically for Post-Covid Hair Health</h2>
                <p>Here is a sample daily diet plan optimized for post-covid hair recovery:</p>

                <p><strong>Morning (empty stomach):</strong> 1 glass of warm water with 1 tablespoon of amla juice and a small amount of honey. <strong>Breakfast:</strong> 2 eggs (or paneer paratha) with 5-6 soaked almonds and 1 glass of milk. <strong>Mid-morning:</strong> 1 fruit such as amla, orange, or pomegranate for Vitamin C and iron. <strong>Lunch:</strong> Lentil soup, spinach or fenugreek vegetable dish, brown rice or roti, salad, and curd. <strong>Evening snack:</strong> Mixed nuts including walnuts, cashews, and pumpkin seeds, along with green tea. <strong>Dinner:</strong> Chicken, fish, or paneer with vegetables, 1 roti, and buttermilk. <strong>Bedtime:</strong> 1 glass of turmeric milk for its anti-inflammatory benefits.</p>

                <p><strong>Daily essentials:</strong> 3-4 litres of water. Vitamin D supplement (after testing). Iron supplement (if deficient). B-complex supplement. For detailed nutrition guidance, read our <a href="vitamins-nutrition-healthy-hair.php">vitamins guide</a>.</p>

                <h2>When Should You See a Doctor? Red Flags to Watch For</h2>
                <p>Post-covid hair fall is usually self-resolving, but professional help is necessary in certain situations:</p>

                <p><strong>No improvement after 6 months:</strong> Telogen Effluvium should typically settle within 6 months. If it has not, there may be an underlying condition at play. <strong>Bald patches:</strong> Telogen Effluvium causes overall thinning, not specific patches. Patches may indicate Alopecia Areata. <strong>Pain, burning, or redness on the scalp:</strong> These symptoms indicate inflammation or infection. <strong>Rapidly thinning hair:</strong> If your ponytail has reduced to half its original thickness or your scalp is clearly visible, immediate evaluation is required. <strong>Overall health is not improving:</strong> Hair fall accompanied by fatigue, weight changes, or mood swings may indicate systemic health issues.</p>

